name: Canterbury Square SW9- AR in public space "Holding the Flame"
description: Augmented Reality statue for Brixton in conversation with Brixton Police station on the legacy of 1981's Uprising. She breaths & tells a challenging story of loss, love & justice. We discuss the potential for AR to tell hidden narratives.

name: DATE CHANGE Chiswick Town Hall
description: Built initially as a vestry, later extended. Victorian and Edwardian interiors with rich tiles and stunning stained glass, one of the most beautiful Victorian interiors in London.

name: Fore Street Art Trail
description: Enjoy a self guided walking tour of Fore Street to see a wide range of public art including murals and sculptures.
address: Fore Street, Angel Edmonton, Enfield, N18 2UE

name: Ingrebourne Valley Visitor Centre
description: Ingrebourne Valley Visitor Centre, at Hornchurch Country Park, the Former RAF Hornchurch Airfield.

name: OmniDe
description: OmniDe is a two floors 100m2 office space conceived as a laboratory where Art, Design and Architecture live together. What we designed is a space that is born from the conversion of an existing accountant space into an architecture office.

name: Yorkton Workshops
description: Yorkton Workshops was restored from a series of dilapidated Victorian stables into a new permanent studio, archive and workshop for Pearson Lloyd. The space also provides a gallery, event space and location available for hire.
